{{BLP sources|date=March 2010}}
{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] --> | name = J. J. Benítez | image = Juan_Jose_Benítez,_2011.jpg | caption = Benítez in 2011 | birth_name = Juan José Benítez | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1946|9|7|mf=y}} | birth_place = [[Pamplona, Spain]] | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = [[Novelist]] | notableworks = The ''[[Caballo de Troya]]'' series | nationality = Spanish | period = 1975 - present | genre = [[Science fiction]], [[Essay]]s | subject = | movement = | influences = | influenced = | signature = | website = {{URL|www.planetabenitez.com}} }} '''Juan José Benítez López''', born September 7, 1946, in the city of [[Pamplona]], [[Navarre]], is a [[Spain|Spanish]] author.
==Career== Benítez received a journalism degree from the [[University of Navarra]] in 1965 and started his work as a journalist in the newspaper ''La Verdad'' of [[Murcia]] in January 1966. Over the next few years he became interested in, and commenced research on, in the [[UFO]] phenomena. After holding jobs at several other newspapers, he left journalism in the late 1970s in order to study [[Ufology]]<ref>[https://www.google.com/search?q=j.+j.+benitez&btnG=Buscar+libros&tbm=bks&tbo=1&hl=es#hl=es&q=inauthor:%22J.+J.+Ben%C3%ADtez+Ben%C3%ADtez,+J.+J.%22&tbm=bks J.J. BENITEZ, Libros, obras, biografía y más en Google Books]</ref>
During his three decades as an author, he has published more than fifty books, including investigative reports, essays, novels and poetry, and sold more than nine million copies worldwide, over five million of them in the ''[[Caballo de Troya]]'' series. He created the television documentary series ''Planeta Encantado'' (Enchanted Planet), for which he traveled to seventeen countries in expound upon his theories as to great unsolved mysteries.<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0073183/ Juan José Benítez - IMDb]</ref>
He currently resides in the coastal town of [[Barbate]], [[Andalusia]], with his wife and two dogs.<ref>[https://www.amazon.com/dp/8408063014 Amazon.com: Caballo de Troya 7 (Nahum) (Spanish Edition) (9788408063018): Juan Jose Benitez: Books]</ref>
