'''Tishynah Buffalo''' is an Indigenous [[fashion design]]er from [[Alexander First Nation]] in Canada but now residing in [[Gordon First Nation]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/edmonton/indigenous-designer-alberta-london-fashion-week-1.3966430|title=Albertan Indigenous designer to showcase culture during London Fashion Week {{!}} CBC News|work=CBC|access-date=2018-08-31|language=en-US}}</ref> Buffalo is perhaps best known for making [[Pendleton jacket]]s with a modern twist.<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2017/02/08/tishynah-buffalo_n_14636468.html|title=Tishynah Buffalo, Alberta Designer, Heads To London Fashion Week To Show Off Cree Culture|date=2017-02-08|work=HuffPost Canada|access-date=2018-08-31|language=en-CA}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite news|url=http://www.couturefashionweek.com/tishynah-buffalo-couture-fashion-week/|title=Tishynah Buffalo Blends Modern and Traditional-Couture Fashion Week|date=2016-08-26|work=Couture Fashion Week|access-date=2018-08-31|language=en-US}}</ref> Her work has been shown at a number of fashion shows such as Fashion Speaks Regina, Western Canada Fashion Week, International Indigenous Fashion Week, and Couture Fashion Week in [[New York City]].<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" />

